(2) When $k \geq 2$, we have $a_{k}^{2}=\frac{1}{(3 k-2)^{2}}<\frac{1}{(3 k-4)(3 k-1)}=\frac{1}{3}\left(\frac{1}{3 k-4}-\frac{1}{3 k-1}\right)$.
Therefore, when $n \geq 2$, we have
$$
\begin{array}{c}
\sum_{k=1}^{n} a_{k}^{2}=1+\sum_{k=2}^{n} a_{k}^{2}<1+\frac{1}{3}\left(\left(\frac{1}{2}-\frac{1}{5}\right)+\left(\frac{1}{5}-\frac{1}{8}\right)+\cdots+\left(\frac{1}{3 n-4}-\frac{1}{3 n-1}\right)\right) \\
