$$\begin{aligned}
& \sum_{c y c} \sqrt{\frac{1}{1+a}} \leqslant 2 \sqrt{1+\frac{1}{(1+a)(1+b)(1+c)}} \\
\Leftrightarrow & \sum_{c y c} \sqrt{\frac{x}{x+y}} \leqslant 2 \sqrt{1+\frac{x y z}{(x+y)(x+z)(y+z)}}
\end{aligned}$$

Since $f(x)=\sqrt{x}$ is a convex function, by Jensen's inequality we have
$$\begin{aligned}
& \sum_{\mathrm{cyc}} \sqrt{\frac{x}{x+y}}=\sum_{\mathrm{cyc}} \frac{x+z}{2} \sqrt{\frac{4 x}{(x+y)(x+z)^{2}}} \\
\leqslant & \sqrt{\sum_{\mathrm{cyc}} \frac{2 x}{(x+y)(x+z)}}=\sqrt{\sum_{\mathrm{cyc}} \frac{2 x(x+y+z)}{(x+y)(x+z)}} \\
= & 2 \sqrt{1+\frac{x y z}{(x+y)(x+z)(y+z)}}
\end{aligned}$$

Therefore, the original inequality holds.

